Usage

  In order to generate images from PlantUML description add the plantuml plugin to your build:

---
<project>
    ...
    <dependencies>
        ...
        <dependency>
            <groupId>${project.groupId}</groupId>
            <artifactId>${project.artifactId}</artifactId>
            <version>${project.version}</version>
        </dependency>
        ...
    </dependencies>
    ...
</project>
---

Configure the plugin

  Specify files to be processed and output directory:

---
<project>
    ...
    <plugins>
        ...
        <plugin>
            ...
            <configuration>
                <sourceFiles>
                    <directory>${basedir}</directory>
                    <includes>
                        <include>
                            src/main/java/**/*.java
                        </include>
                    </includes>
                </sourceFiles>
                <outputDirectory>
                    ${basedir}/target/documentation/img
                </outputDirectory>
            </configuration>
            ...
        </plugin>
        ...
    </plugins>
    ...
</project>
---

* Output in same directory as source file

  By setting the configuration option <<<outputInSourceDirectory>>> to true, 
  the images will be generated in the same directory as the source file. This is useful for
  using PlantUML diagrams in Javadoc, as described here: 
  {{{http://plantuml.sourceforge.net/javadoc.html}http://plantuml.sourceforge.net/javadoc.html}}.
  When this option is set to true, <<<outputDirectory>>> is ignored. Example configuration:
  
---
<configuration>
    <sourceFiles>
        <directory>${basedir}</directory>
        <includes>
          <include>
              src/main/java/**/*.java
          </include>
        </includes>
    </sourceFiles>
    <outputInSourceDirectory>
    	true
    </outputInSourceDirectory>
</configuration>
---

Run goal

  Then execute command:
  
---
mvn clean com.github.jeluard:maven-plantuml-plugin:generate
---

  Find more details about the generate goal {{{./generate-mojo.html}here}}.
